2500|$|In March 2005, Santorum {{expressed}} misgivings <b>about</b> <b>the</b> <b>death</b> <b>penalty</b> {{in light}} of wrongly convicted individuals who were sentenced to death. He went on to say, [...] "I agree with the Pope that in the civilized world ... {{the application of the}} death penalty should be limited. I would definitely agree with that. I would certainly suggest there probably should be some further limits on what we use it for." [...] In January 2012, Santorum said, [...] "when there is certainty, that's the case that capital punishment can be used", but [...] "if there is not certainty, under the law, it shouldn't be used." ...|$|E
