50|$|There {{has been}} {{continuing}} attention for the Carr brothers' case because of various rulings <b>about</b> <b>the</b> Kansas <b>death</b> <b>penalty</b> law and decisions by its high court on such cases. In 2004 the Kansas Supreme Court overturned <b>the</b> state's <b>death</b> <b>penalty</b> law, but <b>the</b> {{state attorney general}} appealed this ruling to the U.S. Supreme Court. It upheld the constitutionality of <b>the</b> state's <b>death</b> <b>penalty</b> law, which returned the Carrs and other condemned killers to death row.|$|R
